The Chronicle Mthabisi Tshuma, Showbiz Correspondent INDOSAKUSA: The Morning Star member Nomore Allah Sibanda is set to drop his debut solo album sometime next week. The eight-track album titled Indaba Zabantu was produced at Elephant Herd Records by award-winning producer Godwin Ndlovu aka Smallz. <img class="wp-image-532097 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/02/Nomore-Allah-Sibanda-1.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/02/Nomore-Allah-Sibanda-1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/02/Nomore-Allah-Sibanda-1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Nomore Allah Sibanda The tracks are Amalobolo, Another chance, Ngizobuyela, Ukwenzil’okubi, Anginay’ubaba, Nguwe, Indaba zabantu and Uzobuya Nini. Sibanda who released singles Uzobuya Nini and Wemali last year as an introduction to his solo career said the forthcoming album is a way to solidify his brand. – @mthabisi_mthire